    @Deprecated
public class RealDistConstant
extends DiscreteDistConstant<java.lang.Double>
implements RealDist
    Real number constant "pseudo"-distribution returns a single constant predefined double value. This "distribution" is most useful for testing purposes. The value to be returned can be specified at construction time.
    See Also:

        public RealDistConstant(Model owner,
                        java.lang.String name,
                        double constantValue,

        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a simple poisson distributed pseudo random generator with the given value as mean of the distribution. Only positive values are allowed.
        Parameters:
        owner - Model : The distribution's owner
        name - java.lang.String : The distribution's name
        constantValue - double : The constant double value produced by this distribution
        showInReport - boolean : Flag for producing reports
        showInTrace - boolean : Flag for producing trace output
